		<title>06INDUSTRY</title>
		<content> The garment manufacture described on  
 page 5 are mainly packed in cardboard 
 boxes for despatch to mail order      
 depots all over the country.The firm  
 employs 160 mainly female staff-90 are
 machinists and 45 back up.The other 25
 are management and office staff.The   
 machinists are paid a basic wage with 
 a bonus scheme coming into effect     
 after a predetermined standard is     
 reached.                              
 About 1 percent of output is sold in a
 small shop next to the factory.       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
